alternative_parents.description: Aromatic compounds that are made up of carbon and hydrogen atoms only.
alternative_parents.name: Aromatic hydrocarbons

alternative_parents.description: Polycyclic organic compounds made up only of carbon and hydrogen atoms.
alternative_parents.name: Polycyclic hydrocarbons

class.description: Hydrocarbons that contains one or more unsaturated carbon atoms. These compounds contain one or more double, triple, or aromatic bonds.
class.name: Unsaturated hydrocarbons

description: This compound belongs to the class of organic compounds known as azulenes. These are polycyclic aromatic compounds containing the azulene skeleton, which consists of the cyclopentadiene ring fused to a cycloheptadiene ring.

direct_parent.description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing the azulene skeleton, which consists of the cyclopentadiene ring fused to a cycloheptadiene ring.
direct_parent.name: Azulenes

intermediate_nodes.description: Olefins that contain at least one ring in their structure.
intermediate_nodes.name: Cyclic olefins

kingdom.description: Compounds that contain at least one carbon atom, excluding isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, Carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.
kingdom.name: Organic compounds

subclass.description: Acyclic and cyclic hydrocarbons having one or more carbon-carbon double bonds, apart from the formal ones in aromatic compounds. The class of olefins subsumes alkenes and cycloalkenes and the corresponding polyenes.
subclass.name: Olefins

superclass.description: Organic compounds made up only of carbon and hydrogen atoms.
superclass.name: Hydrocarbons
